description: 1Ô∏è‚É£A chunk of dense fur off of a beast or something.
name: Dense Pelt

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£A pelt found under the ghastly aura of a wisp.
It is almost like touching a glowing bunny.
name: Wisp Pelt

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£A vividly bright pelt of unnatural brightness and glory.
Was this monster you harvested this from a spawn from Dionysis or something?
name: Bright Pelt

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£A gorgeous and shimmering pelt from a truly magnificent speciman.
Even the deities would be jealous of a mortal wearing something JAFTED from this.
name: Radiant Pelt

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£Even now that the beast you've scalped this off of is dead,
the fur of the pelt still almost looks like its flowing with some kind of ethereal wind.
name: Flowing Pelt

description: 1Ô∏è‚É£Some quills still on the pelt are barely hangin' in there.
name: Loose Spines

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£The pelt is almost as red as the quills, but at least
the quills aren't falling out.
name: Red Spines

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£Still intact and almost functional, the quills on this pelt are
surprisingly sharp for being dead for who knows how long.
name: Sharp Spines

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£Crimson like the blood they will draw if you come anywhere fucking
near these spikey boiz.
name: Crimson Spines

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£The pelt this animal came off of requires a special carrying case
due to the fact that the spines can poke holes into another dimension.
name: Quantum Spines

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£This is literally just a dead branch that some plant monster
probably dropped. Why did you pick it up?
name: Dead Branch

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£A branch that is a bit dry, but otherwise relatively sturdy.
It could probably be used for JAFTING in some way.
name: Dry Branch

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£A branch that appears to have been preserved or something,
because it is definitely old, but still kinda firm.
name: Preserved Branch

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£A branch that was hardened as though it was recently mined
out from a 74 layers deep archaeological dig.
name: Hard Branch

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£The branch at this point is not even really a branch, and also
somehow sings. This makes no sense, but you keep it anyway.
name: Lark Branch

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£The horn off of a deceased bull or minataur most likely.
Because you roughed 'em up, its horn is also broken.
name: Broken Horn

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£A horn that is slightly cracked, likely from the concussive blow you left
the original owner with upon goring off their body.
name: Cracked Horn

description: 3Ô∏è‚É£A rather long horn, still intact surprisingly, and kinda sharp.
name: Long Horn

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£A horn off a world-renowned demon that surely felt great shame when you ripped off
their only way of compensating for their size.
name: Demon Horn

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£A mighty horn glimmering and sparkling due to the studded gems.
Yes, you read that right: this is a diamond-encrusted horn.
name: Regal Horn

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£These greens were probably alive once, but they were trampled
all over, shit on, and half-digested. They are actually very gross.
name: Dead Greens

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£A pile of leafy greens, petals, and other flora from the
bottom-most layer of a forest.
name: Leafy Greens

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£Unusually bouncy greens that you plucked from somewhere that you maybe shouldn't have.
Why are they bouncing? The world will never know.
name: Bouncy Greens

description: 4Ô∏è‚É£A mighty fine bunch of green greens.
name: Fine Greens

description: 5Ô∏è‚É£The most greenest of green greenery that you ever did green.
name: Verdant Greens

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£The stinger of a fallen enemy. Cracked to all hell because you
find it difficult to show restraint against such pitiful mobs.
name: Cracked Needle

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£Not very different from the \Armor[327], except that it
isn't cracked.
name: Intact Stinger

description: 3Ô∏è‚É£A very pointy and sharp stinger that will do sharp stinger things as-needed.
name: Sharp Stinger

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£A ruthless stinger you barely escaped with your life with after ripping off the ass of
one of those stupid ass bees. They deserved it though, I promise.
name: Offensive Stinger

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£It is as though this stinger has muscles built into it, as it is still writhing and
twitching. Is it alive?!
name: Live Stinger

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£It isn't clear what this is, because it smells absolutely like nothing.
You probably should be cautious how you use this.
name: Odorless Powder

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£Now that it can be smelled, it is undecided as to which is worse:
being able to smell it, or not being able to smell it.
name: Odorful Powder

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£A truly ghastly-smelling powder that you probably should not have picked up.
Why did you pick up a pile of this anyway? It is literal death.
name: Ghastly Powder

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£This death powder- in addition to smelling rancid- also appears to be glowing
with the regret of 1000 wishes left unfulfilled.
name: Spectral Powder

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£This powder is not just hard to grasp, but also hard to see due to it being
almost entirely invisible... but the smell. Ohhhh the smell. Sweet fucking hell it is awful.
name: Transparent Powder

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£Your average everyday stone. These things have a multitude of
uses, but you can do what you want with it.
name: Worn Stone

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£This \Armor[336] has been extra worn, as it is starting to get kinda round
and smooth on the edges.
name: Round Stone

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£Rather than becoming even more round, the stone became more disk-like actually.
How strange to find such abnormalities in nature.
name: Circular Stone

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£It is unclear why you are now picking up such obscure-shaped stones off the ground.
Though, they do appear to grant some degree of benefit in JAFTING.
name: Trapezoidal Stone

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£A stone that is a perfect sphere. It probably isn't even a stone to be honest.
It is likely some kind of highly advanced artifact of a time long past.
name: Spherical Stone

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£Coral is brutally sharp when dry, and also brutally fragile.
So be careful!
name: Dry Coral

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£A branch of really gnarly coral.
Like totally tubular dude!
name: Gnarled Coral

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£The kind of coral you probably see kappas holding onto for some unknown reason.
They must miss their rivers, and here you are farming them for their home's keepsakes.
name: River Coral

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£When coral grows a lot, it starts to layer upon itself.
It doesn't actually do this in any known science, but around here that seems to be the case.
name: Layered Coral

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£The coral that literally is growing off of a kappa- that you just slayed.
How else will you JAFT awesome lucky things without this?
name: Kapn Coral

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£The meat of this tail is almost entirely removed. It is barely possible to even
tell that this was a tail to begin with. Why did you pick it up?
name: Scavenged Tail

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£The tail from some kind of monster in the area.
The meat is absolutely worthless to cook with.
name: Sinewy Tail

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£Do not mistake the name for this being a thick and juicy tail.
There appears to be actual beef(!!!) or beef-like meat on this tail left.
name: Beefy Tail

description: 4Ô∏è‚É£This tail has some serious oomph to it.
name: Thicc Tail

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£While the tail does have some sort of scales still attached, it is clear that you have
the means to penetrate the scales, so who cares? Itadakimasu!
name: Dargin Tail

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£Even as busted as this talon is, its still very pointy and
can probably do some damage.
name: Busted Talon

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£A talon still intact, but rather dull. Still dangerous, but
not as dangerous as the ones still attached to the owner.
name: Dull Talon

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£Dangerously hooked, this talon is fully intact and probably could cause
some damage if you tried to use it that way.
name: Hooked Talon

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£A talon with micro-serrations all across the talon. This is very deadly
to have produced intact, hopefully it was worth it.
name: Serrated Talon

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£A wildly deadly talon with edges, hooks, blades, dripping with poison,
glowing with otherworldly power... Who knows what you would use this for.
name: Lethal Talon

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£The eye has been severed from its connective tissue that
is required for most uses, making this mostly useless.
name: Detached Eyeball

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£An eyeball of which has been gravely sliced from edge to edge.
Even if this was attached, which its not, it would not be of great use.
name: Lacerated Eyeball

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£This eyeball does not appear to require a host, it floats about on its
own, but seems content to reside in your endless item sack.
name: Snooping Eyeball

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£Instead of floating mysteriously, it just spins its connective tissue
around at insane speeds like a helicopter blade, forcing levitation.
name: Helicopter Eyeball

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£This eye clearly is able to see through not only you, but also through
your family and friends and probably walls and clothing.
name: Peerless Eyeball

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£A pair of fangs that are so flimsy, they might actually be
made of jelly. Did you get this from a Jelli?
name: Flimsy Fangs

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£Due to the fact that these incisors are made of bone, it is
tough to determine whether they are teeth, or mandibles.
name: Bone Fangs

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£A pair of fangs that are strong and capable of piercing flesh.
Obviously not yours, though, since you walk away the victor with them in-hand.
name: Double Fangs

description: 4Ô∏è‚É£A mighty set of fangs, likely from a dragon or maybe a wolf.
name: Powerful Fangs

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£Extremely sharp fangs that are quite possibly the sharpest thing you've ever
obtained. Even your item sack is concerned about being sliced open from these.
name: Razor Fangs

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£The femur from a large animal- that must've been totally
obliterated based on how much is left of this bone.
name: Old Bone

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£A femur of some kind of humanoid that has long since been deceased.
It appears to be cracked beyond repair.
name: Mossy Bone

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£A femur that likely came from a large feline of some sort.
It appears completely intact.
name: Earthen Bone

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£A massive femur that could only have come from something equivalent to
a titan.
name: Petrified Bone

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£It is unclear what entity this femur belongs to, as it is completely intact
but also kind of elastic.
name: Spiral Bone

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£Some kind of animal blood that has been dried for a while.
This is the result of a bit of rain loosening it so you can pick it up.
name: Dried Blood

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£After bleeding a while, blood will start to coagulate and get thick.
This is that blood, its actually kinda gross that you picked this off some beast.
name: Coagulated Blood

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£Probably not from an actual virgin, but instead from one of those harpies
that are called "virgins" up in the mountains.
name: Virgin Blood

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£This is some really evil-looking blood. Why did you pick it up?
It is probably haunted or something.
name: Sinister Blood

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£The finest of fine things across the land- blue blood.
Only the royalest of royals carry this blood.
name: Blue Blood

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£These scales are still attached to a membrane, but some are
actually starting to fall off.
name: Loose Scales

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£These appear to be associated with some sort of lizard, but
after you fully destroyed the original owner, its tough to remember.
name: Lizard Scales

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£Some rather durable scales off a dragon or something otherwise that is
identifiable as "durable".
name: Enduring Scales

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£The scales off of a wurm deep deep in the subterranean depths.
The scales are difficult to see due to their inexplicable absorption of light.
name: Wurm Scales

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£The mightiest of mighty, scales off a dargin have all sorts of benefits,
including the ability to avoid crits.
name: Dargin Scales

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£This root is outrageously durable for how withered and busted
it looks.
name: Tough Root

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£A root that is sprouting little tendrils out, though they appear
to be extensions of the root rather than flowers.
name: Sprouting Root

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£A root that has been petrified in some kind of stone for likely millenia.
The durability it boasts can be used for a variety of purposes.
name: Petrified Root

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£A root that is rather long, clearly one that ran deep deep into
the ground. Perhaps you should put it back so it can grow more?
name: Deep Root

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£The root of the ages, reaching through both dirt and the spacetime continuum.
Legends say it eventually reaches back to itself through dimensions.
name: Infinity Root

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£Bearcat meat is well-known for being terrible in flavor, gamey as all hell,
and like chewing through leather at any temp of cook.
name: Bearcat Flank

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£The flank of a beast that looks like its been ripped off-
probably with bare hands- from the animal it once resided on.
name: Ripped Flank

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£When it comes to premium flank cuts, you always look to the White.
Though the White can be tough to hunt, its flank is worth its weight in G.
name: White Flank

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£The volt jelli is a fiercesome jelli, but its flank will melt in your mouth.
The Raevula population is kept in check by deaths from attempting to hunt these beach demons.
name: Volt Jelli Flank

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£Of course the finest flank is none other than the gigacat's flank.
Lean, but due to its apex predator status, has the finest choice of prey to give it that perfect marbling.
name: Gigacat Flank

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£An imp's tongue is most commonly used in a variety of
witch's tinctures. Their sense of taste supposedly makes brews taste better.
name: Imp Tongue

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£The counterfeit alternative to \Item[391]s are obviously the super common
goblin tongues. Nevermind that goblins don't exist in this game.
name: Goblin Tongue

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£The tongue of a froggo is notoriously long and elastic. You could probably
use this in alchemy or something to JAFT the finest potions.
name: Froggo Tongue

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£The tongue of a since-passed scholar, but you decided it would be somehow
more beneficial to rip the tongue out and use it for JAFTING.
name: Dying Tongue

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£The emptiness radiates strongly off of this tongue. Clearly the most
maleficant of words not even an M-rated game would permit to be written in this text box were spoken with it.
name: Sinister Tongue

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£Though the ribs and rib meat all look intact, the animal you
chose to destroy to get these ribs must've been nearly starved.
name: Boney Ribs

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£The ribs of a super long lamia.
As a result, there are a fuckton of them.
name: Lamia Ribs

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£The serpent's ribs are usually kind of flexible due to the need to
constantly be wriggling.
name: Serpent Ribs

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£The need to combine bovine and serpent resulted in the "moosnake".
It is unknown why this was created, but tastes kinda like hamburger.
name: Moosnake Ribs

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£Eternally self-consuming ribs that make no sense.
Just accept that they are top-tier and probably used to JAFT some really nice things.
name: Ouroboros Ribs

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£Slime monsters keep it all together with the power of science!
And also gelatin.
name: Big Gelatin

description: 2Ô∏è‚É£You must've plucked this glob from a rather large slime, because this is also rather large.
name: Large Gelatin

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£A huge ass glob of gelatin probably carved from a kingly slime or something.
It strangely has no smell.
name: Huge Gelatin

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£A truly massive speciman of a slime.
It is unclear how you are keeping this in your bag, much less multiple of them.
name: Massive Gelatin

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£This slime glob is actually bigger than you.
Do not question logic, just collect as many as possible, they must be important.
name: Colossal Gelatin

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£The veil of the dead keeps ghosts at bay... or so the legend goes.
Really we just wanted something from the ghostys.
name: Inert Veil

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£The veil of the dead keeps ghosts at bay... or so the legend goes.
Really we just wanted something from the ghostys.
name: Dead Veil

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£The veil of the dead keeps ghosts at bay... or so the legend goes.
Really we just wanted something from the ghostys.
name: Expired Veil

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£The veil of the dead keeps ghosts at bay... or so the legend goes.
Really we just wanted something from the ghostys.
name: Perished Veil

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£The veil of the dead keeps ghosts at bay... or so the legend goes.
Really we just wanted something from the ghostys.
name: Wasted Veil

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£This is pretty gross to actually carry around, much less carry multiple around.
It is bloody, wet, squishy, and is starting to smell bad.
name: Animal Heart

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£The heart of your foes serves as a fine prize for their defeat.
There are probably other uses, beyond holding it proudly.
name: Beast Heart

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£A heart from the aquatic sort are strange and more core-like or something.
It is certainly pulsing still; you should probably store it while it still can exist outside of water.
name: Hydro Heart

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£Giant hearts are just massive and extremely heavy. Carrying more than one of these,
in your item sack no less, is a truly legendary feat to its own, nevermind defeating them for this.
name: Titan Heart

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£The old classic dargin heart never fails to let down. It is a massive and
cute dragon-shaped heart. Does that make sense? Not at all, but here we are.
name: Dargin Heart

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£A large blob of green slime shit you scooped up from a slime.
You can't even eat it its so fucking gross looking and feeling.
name: Gross Slime

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£This slime is pretty gross. It was leftover from one of the
countless slime monsters you've slain. Still sorta jiggly, though.
name: Leftover Slime

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£The ways in english of saying "this is gross" are countless.
But this slime is downright nasty, offending all 8 of your senses.
name: Slimy Slime

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£The power of smell offends you in ways you didn't think were possible.
This slime is both rancid to look at and smell- it is a mystery why you carry it still.
name: Putrid Slime

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£Today you learned that slime eventually will smell like nothing.
You just need to age it several thousand years first.
name: Ancient Slime

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£A wing from some kind of flying critter that has clearly been
damaged beyond repair.
name: Damaged Wing

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£A wing that is still flapping, despite you having removed it from its
original owner.
name: Flappy Wing

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£Likely from a faerie of some kind, this wing is almost glossy in
its appearance due to a toxin the wing's pores emit in self-defense.
name: Glossy Wing

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£A large wing that appears to be actually two wings that work
together to accomplish flight. This monster must've grown two wings from one joint.
name: Double Wing

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£A perfectly intact wing that sparkles all colors of the rainbow.
It smells faintly of potatoes.
name: Iridescent Wing

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£It appears to be a standard freshwater cod.
What a surprise that this planet has some of the same fish as Earth.
name: Freshwater Cod

description: 2Ô∏è‚É£A beautiful trout that probably lived in some nearby lake.
name: Lake Trout

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£A giant bass that likely was found in some nearby river.
Its scales glisten in the sunlight- probably because its still wet.
name: River Bass

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£When salmon are grown in saltwater, their skin gets tougher, but
the flesh tastes even more delicious.
name: Saltwater Salmon

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£An entire tuna that has must've come from the ocean.
It is colossal, and a mystery how you are storing this in your item sack.
name: Ocean Tuna

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£Most would believe these are the wings of a faerie, but really it
is a petal- literally a flake from their flesh.
name: Faerie Petal

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£The bud of a faerie is basically just a premature bit of the faerie
that you really shouldn't be harvesting, you monster.
name: Faerie Bud

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£The flower of a faerie is available any time after the faerie has
reached adulthood, but only a small window is available for the blossom...
name: Faerie Flower

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£A beautiful blossom of a faerie. This only becomes available
when the faeries are at peak maturity.
name: Faerie Blossom

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£The bouquet is just five dozen faerie blossoms. Why in the world would
anyone need this?
name: Faerie Bouquet

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£They are wiggling, slimy, and extra tiny. These are quite possibly
the grossest thing you've carried around on purpose.
name: Bug Eggs

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£Tiny critters like raccoons or squirrels are known to emerge from them
in this land.
name: Critter Eggs

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£The classic of classic, eggs from a bird.
You can use these for all sorts of fine cookery.
name: Avian Eggs

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£The eggs from a froggo are much like what you recall coming from regular frogs.
Tadpoles come from these if left unattended, so attend them!
name: Froggo Eggs

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£Did you think ghostys around here were the spirits of the dead?
They are living creatures just like you and me, but cute and spooky.
name: Ghosty Eggs

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£The ear from some kind of humanoid. Often fashioned into a very
stylish necklace in certain cultures, but this one is just waxxy and gross.
name: Waxxy Ear

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£An ear that has been pierced a few times. In some cultures, it is normal to do that.
In others, it is just inefficient, and thus the pierced-ear-bearers are exterminated.
name: Pierced Ear

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£One whole and complete ear.
It almost looks kinda like yours.
name: Complete Ear

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£When the bandit first approached you, you decided instead of listening that
just chopping their ear off was a better opening statement.
name: Bandit's Ear

description: 5Ô∏è‚É£The ear of the lordiest lord in all the land.
name: Lord's Ear

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£One of the 8 vines a wolftrap possesses. The plant has a ton of great
nutritional benefits, but is best known for restoring mental accuity.
name: Wolftrap Vine

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£One of the 8 vines a bloodtrap possesses. Contrary to the
wolftrap, many of the components of a bloodtrap are mostly toxic.
name: Bloodtrap Vine

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£A vine from one of the 4 vines a subtrap possesses. Its vines are extremely elastic
and could probably be used as a rope if you really wanted.
name: Subtrap Vine

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£A vine from one of the 6 vines a voidtrap possesses. Its vines are deadly
due to their matter-displacement-on-contact molecular reaction.
name: Voidtrap Vine

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£The vine from one of the deadliest flora known on this planet.
Just by keeping it in your item sack, it is trying to shift your fate towards doom.
name: Doomtrap Vine

description:
1Ô∏è‚É£The core of some sort of energy-based being.
Except that its completely faded and looks not far off from a regular rock.
name: Faded Core

description:
2Ô∏è‚É£A magical core that still glows faintly, but really can't deliver a lot.
Maybe you can charge it somehow?
name: Dimmed Core

description:
3Ô∏è‚É£The official core of a magic entity that derives its power from raw energy.
This is basically their battery, and you stole it from them.
name: Magic Core

description:
4Ô∏è‚É£A core still brimming with the energy of the enemy you just ripped it from.
It could probably power a lot of things!
name: Pulsating Core

description:
5Ô∏è‚É£A brilliantly glowing core, overflowing with an abundance of energy!
Probably has equivalent energy output to a star going supernova.
name: Radiant Core
